verses.text_plain: Not unto us, O Lord, not unto us, but unto thy name give glory, for thy mercy, and for thy truth’s sake.
verses.verse_html: 1Not unto us, O Lord, not unto us, but unto thy name give glory, for thy mercy, and for thy truth’s sake.

tokens.text: not unto us, but unto thy name

verses.text_plain: Wherefore should the heathen say, Where is now their God?
verses.verse_html: 2Wherefore should the heathen say, Where is now their God?

verses.text_plain: But our God is in the heavens: he hath done whatsoever he hath pleased.
verses.verse_html: 3But our God is in the heavens: he hath done whatsoever he hath pleased.

verses.text_plain: Their idols are silver and gold, the work of men’s hands.
verses.verse_html: 4Their idols are silver and gold, the work of men’s hands.

verses.text_plain: They have mouths, but they speak not: eyes have they, but they see not:
verses.verse_html: 5They have mouths, but they speak not: eyes have they, but they see not:

verses.text_plain: They have ears, but they hear not: noses have they, but they smell not:
verses.verse_html: 6They have ears, but they hear not: noses have they, but they smell not:

verses.text_plain: They have hands, but they handle not: feet have they, but they walk not: neither speak they through their throat.
verses.verse_html: 7They have hands, but they handle not: feet have they, but they walk not: neither speak they through their throat.

verses.text_plain: They that make them are like unto them; so is every one that trusteth in them.
verses.verse_html: 8They that make them are like unto them; so is every one that trusteth in them.

verses.text_plain: O Israel, trust thou in the Lord: he is their help and their shield.
verses.verse_html: 9O Israel, trust thou in the Lord: he is their help and their shield.

verses.text_plain: O house of Aaron, trust in the Lord: he is their help and their shield.
verses.verse_html: 10O house of Aaron, trust in the Lord: he is their help and their shield.

verses.text_plain: Ye that fear the Lord, trust in the Lord: he is their help and their shield.
verses.verse_html: 11Ye that fear the Lord, trust in the Lord: he is their help and their shield.

verses.text_plain: The Lord hath been mindful of us: he will bless us; he will bless the house of Israel; he will bless the house of Aaron.
verses.verse_html: 12The Lord hath been mindful of us: he will bless us; he will bless the house of Israel; he will bless the house of Aaron.

verses.text_plain: He will bless them that fear the Lord, both small and great.
verses.verse_html:
13He will bless them that fear the Lord, both small and great. ▼
▼ and: Heb. with

verses.text_plain: The Lord shall increase you more and more, you and your children.
verses.verse_html: 14The Lord shall increase you more and more, you and your children.

tokens.text: you more and more, you and your children

verses.text_plain: Ye are blessed of the Lord which made heaven and earth.
verses.verse_html: 15Ye are blessed of the Lord which made heaven and earth.

verses.text_plain: The heaven, even the heavens, are the Lord’s: but the earth hath he given to the children of men.
verses.verse_html: 16The heaven, even the heavens, are the Lord’s: but the earth hath he given to the children of men.

verses.text_plain: The dead praise not the Lord, neither any that go down into silence.
verses.verse_html: 17The dead praise not the Lord, neither any that go down into silence.

verses.text_plain: But we will bless the Lord from this time forth and for evermore. Praise the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 18But we will bless the Lord from this time forth and for evermore. Praise the Lord.

tokens.text: from this time forth and for
